_meanings:
Teaching, instructing, lecturing, especially
on sacred knowledge; one of the 

six duties of a Brāhmaṇa. 
According to Indian law-givers {#aDyApana#} is
of three kinds: (1) undertaken
for charity, (2) for wages and (3)
in consideration of services 
rendered; <ab>cf.</ab> <ls>Hārīta</ls>: {#aDyApanaM ca triviDaM#} 
{#DarmArTamfkTakAraRam . SuSrUzAkaraRaM ceti triviDaM#}
